			<div class="infosubhead"><a name="c_levels"></a>Gateway Badging Types</div>
			<p>IoC currently support the following gateway badging alignment types:</p>
			<p style="margin-left:50px;">
			<ul>
			<li><strong>Attendance</strong> – The badge represents attendance.  To earn this badge the recipient must attend an event.</li>
			<li><strong>Knowledge Self-Assessed</strong> – This badge represents knowledge of a domain. To earn this badge the recipient must have self-assessed their knowledge of a domain set by an event or course</li>
			<li><strong>Knowledge Bronze</strong> – This badge represents a basic knowledge of a domain. To earn this badge the recipient must show evidence of a basic knowledge of a domain.</li>
			<li><strong>Knowledge Silver</strong> – This badge represents an intermediate knowledge of a domain. To earn this badge the recipient must show evidence of an intermediate knowledge of a domain.</li>
			<li><strong>Knowledge Gold</strong> – This badge represents a confident knowledge of a domain. To earn this badge the recipient must show evidence of a confident knowledge of a domain</li>
			</ul>
		
			<p>IoC Alignment badge images:</p>
